sql:
SELECT username 
FROM users 
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM favorites);

SELECT name, rating 
FROM facilities 
WHERE rating > (SELECT AVG(rating) FROM facilities);

external_knowledge:
- "general feedback scores" in the question refers to the average rating of each facility;
- "review counts" refers to the number of reviews for each facility;
- "identities" in this context refer to the unique identifiers of each facility, or 'facility_id'.

- "glowing beacons of excellence" metaphorically refers to facilities with high ratings;
- "prolific scribes of reviews" are users who have written a large number of reviews (more than 10 reviews);
- "eloquent voices" refers to the prolific reviewers;
- "shining stars" and "luster" are metaphors for facilities with high ratings.

- "storm guardians" refers to the facility administrators;
- "stood watch over the facility’s horizon" metaphorically means they have reviewed the facility or submitted a review;
- "in the last day" means within the last 24 hours.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM facilities
WHERE address LIKE '%Toronto%' AND rating > 5;

SELECT * 
FROM facilities 
WHERE facility_id NOT IN (SELECT facility_id FROM favorites);

external_knowledge:
- "realm of amenities" metaphorically represents the database of facilities;
- "every stone tells the tale of its type" refers to the facility types and their names;
- "every whisper carries the name of a reviewer" symbolizes the user who provided the review for the facility;
- "names of these establishments" refers to the names of the facilities;
- "services they offer" represents the services provided by each facility;
- "ratings" refer to the average reviews;
- "addresses that mark their territory" symbolizes the physical addresses of the facilities;
- "cartographer mapping the landscape of leisure" metaphorically describes the task of compiling data about facilities, their types, user reviews, services, ratings, and addresses.
